[[Image:SeaUrchin.jpg|thumb|A sea urchin]]
==English==

===Etymology===
[[sea]] + [[urchin]] (meaning [[hedgehog]]), due to the similarity in appearance to the hedgehog.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|sg=[[sea]] [[urchin]]}}

# Any of many [[marine]] [[echinoderm]]s, of the class ''[[Echinoidea]]'', commonly found in shallow water, having a complex [[chewing]] structure named [[Aristotle's lantern]]

